      value-deserializer: org.springframework.kafka.support.serializer.JsonDeserializer
      group-id: payment-processor
      auto-offset-reset: earliest
```

**Advantages**: High throughput (millions msgs/sec), durable storage, horizontal scalability.
**Use Cases**: Event sourcing, real-time analytics, activity tracking, log aggregation.

Kafka Consumer subscribes to topics and processes messages. Consumer behavior depends on group configuration, offsets, and partition assignment.

Consumer Behavior:

1. **Consumer Groups**:
```
Topic: "orders" with 3 partitions
Consumer Group 1 (payment processing):
├─ Consumer 1: Reads partition 0
├─ Consumer 2: Reads partition 1
└─ Consumer 3: Reads partition 2
  (Each partition assigned to one consumer)

Consumer Group 2 (audit logging):
├─ Consumer 4: Reads all partitions
