Event-Driven Architecture decouples services using events. Services publish events when state changes; other services subscribe and react to events.

Traditional vs Event-Driven:

Traditional (Synchronous):
```
Order Service → (REST call) → Payment Service → (wait)
Order Service → (REST call) → Shipping Service → (wait)
If Payment fails: Shipping doesn't happen
Tightly coupled, hard to scale
```

Event-Driven (Asynchronous):
```
Order Service publishes "OrderCreated" event
    ↓
Event Stream (Kafka, RabbitMQ, etc.)
    ├─→ Payment Service subscribes, processes
    ├─→ Shipping Service subscribes, processes
    └─→ Audit Service subscribes, logs

Services loosely coupled, independent scaling
Failures don't block other services
```

