Saga Pattern manages distributed transactions across microservices using coordinated events instead of traditional ACID transactions, ensuring data consistency.

Problem Saga Solves:

```
Two-Phase Commit (problems):
Order Service ↔ Payment Service ↔ Shipping Service
If any service fails, rollback all
Blocking calls, tight coupling, doesn't work across orgs

Saga Solution (decoupled):
Events orchestrate transaction
Services independently process and publish events
If failure: compensating transactions roll back
```

Saga Types:

1. **Choreography-Based** (Event-driven):
```
Step 1: Order Service creates order → publishes OrderCreated event
        ↓
Step 2: Payment Service listens → processes payment → publishes PaymentCompleted
        ↓
Step 3: Shipping Service listens → starts shipping → publishes ShippingStarted
        ↓
If payment fails: publishes PaymentFailed
Step 4: Shipping Service listens → cancels shipping
        Order Service listens → rolls back order
```

Implementation:
```java
@Service
public class OrderService {

    @Autowired
    private OrderRepository orderRepository;
    @Autowired
    private KafkaTemplate<String, OrderEvent> kafkaTemplate;

    @Transactional
    public void createOrder(OrderRequest request) {
        Order order = new Order(request);
        order.setStatus("PENDING");
        orderRepository.save(order);

        kafkaTemplate.send("order-events", 
            new OrderCreatedEvent(order.getId(), order.getUserId()));
    }

    @KafkaListener(topics = "payment-events", groupId = "order-service")
    public void handlePaymentFailed(PaymentFailedEvent event) {
        Order order = orderRepository.findById(event.getOrderId()).orElse(null);
        if (order != null) {
            order.setStatus("CANCELLED");
            orderRepository.save(order);
            // Notify user
        }
    }
}

@Service
public class PaymentService {

    @Autowired
    private PaymentRepository paymentRepository;
    @Autowired
    private KafkaTemplate<String, PaymentEvent> kafkaTemplate;

    @KafkaListener(topics = "order-events", groupId = "payment-service")
    public void handleOrderCreated(OrderCreatedEvent event) {
        try {
            Payment payment = processPayment(event.getOrderId());
            paymentRepository.save(payment);

            kafkaTemplate.send("payment-events",
                new PaymentCompletedEvent(event.getOrderId(), payment.getId()));
        } catch (Exception e) {
            kafkaTemplate.send("payment-events",
                new PaymentFailedEvent(event.getOrderId(), e.getMessage()));
        }
    }
}
```

2. **Orchestration-Based** (Centralized):
```
Saga Orchestrator coordinates all steps
Order Service → Orchestrator → Payment Service
              → Orchestrator → Shipping Service
              → Orchestrator → Notification Service
```

Implementation:
```java
@Service
public class OrderSagaOrchestrator {

    @Autowired
    private PaymentService paymentService;
    @Autowired
    private ShippingService shippingService;
    @Autowired
    private OrderRepository orderRepository;

    public void executeOrderSaga(OrderRequest request) {
        Order order = new Order(request);
        order.setStatus("PENDING");
        orderRepository.save(order);

        try {
            // Step 1: Process Payment
            Payment payment = paymentService.processPayment(order.getId());
            if (payment.isFailed()) {
                compensateOrder(order);
                return;
            }

            // Step 2: Create Shipment
            Shipment shipment = shippingService.createShipment(order.getId());
            if (shipment.isFailed()) {
                paymentService.refundPayment(payment.getId());
                compensateOrder(order);
                return;
            }

            // Step 3: Success
            order.setStatus("COMPLETED");
            orderRepository.save(order);

        } catch (Exception e) {
            // Compensation transactions
            compensateOrder(order);
        }
    }

    private void compensateOrder(Order order) {
        order.setStatus("CANCELLED");
        orderRepository.save(order);
        // Notify user
    }
}
```

Saga States:

```
PENDING
├─→ PAYMENT_PROCESSING
│   ├─→ PAYMENT_COMPLETED → SHIPPING_PROCESSING
│   │                     ├─→ SHIPPING_COMPLETED → COMPLETED
│   │                     └─→ SHIPPING_FAILED → COMPENSATING
│   └─→ PAYMENT_FAILED → COMPENSATING
└─→ COMPENSATING → CANCELLED
```

**Choreography**: Simpler, loosely coupled; harder to debug
**Orchestration**: Centralized, easier to follow; more code, potential bottleneck
**Trade-off**: Saga doesn't guarantee ACID; relies on compensating transactions for rollback.
